\begin_layout Standard
An ontology formally represents knowledge as a set of concepts within a
 domain, and the relationships between those concepts.
 It can be used to reason about the entities within that domain, and may
 be used to describe the domain.
 In theory, an ontology is a "formal, explicit specification of a shared
 conceptualisation"
